  <h2>Creating Users</h2>
  <%= image_tag "new_user_link.png"%>
  <p>To create users, you must be logged in as an administrator. Begin by clicking the "Users" link at the top of your screen. If you do not see this link, you are not signed in as an administrator. This takes you to a list of all the current users. At the bottom of the list, there is a link to "New user". Click this link </p>
  <%= image_tag "new_user_form.png"%>
  <p> You are now looking at the new user form. Fill out the form for the user you want to create. Take note of the username and password you enter, as this will be the log in credentials for this user. Also, make sure you select the correct role for the user. An administrator has full access to all the entries in the application, including attendance and grades. A teacher has access to view their own students and change their grades. A service administrator (svc_admin) can view and update students services attendance. If you indicate that a user is a teacher, you will have the option of associating them with a kitah each time you create a new kitah. Once you are done, click "Create User". The user will be created and you will see the updated list of users. If the user is not created, a message will show at the top of the page explaining why.</p>
